---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro'
---

<Shell
  title="Welcome"
  description="Stylebender: The missing web workflow for fast moving Indie developers."
>
  <div class="container py-5 pb-0">
    <div class="text-secondary text-center my-0">Welcome to stylebender</div>
    <h1 class="mx-auto mt-0 text-center">
      The missing web workflow for the fast moving indie developer
    </h1>

    <div class="text-center">
      <a href="/app" class="cta">Start bending</a>
    </div>

    <div>
      <img
        id="screenshot-light"
        src="/screenshot-light.png"
        alt="Screenshot"
        class="img-fluid"
      />
      <img
        id="screenshot-dark"
        src="/screenshot.png"
        alt="Screenshot"
        class="img-fluid"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="intro py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row mx-md-5">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2 class="fs-6">What is stylebender?</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">
            It simply a style generator. But instead of modifying configuration
            files or using library APIs, you use the browser to visually develop
            your looks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2 class="fs-6">Easy. Dark and light!</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">
            You can skip the Figma stages and dive right in.
          </p>
          <p class="text-secondary">
            You can create styles for both light and dark modes. All CSS, no
            Javascript.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2 class="fs-6">Download and use!</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">
            When you're done, you can download your stylesheet and add to your
            project and get going.
          </p>
          <p class="text-secondary">
            Doesn't matter what web framework you're using.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Shell>

<style>
  h1 {
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .cta {
    border: 0;
    background-color: var(--bs-primary);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #fff;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: inherit;
  }

  #screenshot-light {
    display: block;
  }

  #screenshot-dark {
    display: none;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f6f8fa;
    border-top: 1px solid #e9eaeb;
  }

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    #screenshot-light {
      display: none;
    }

    #screenshot-dark {
      display: block;
    }

    .intro {
      background: #1d1d1d;
      border-top: 1px solid #3f3f3f;
    }
  }
</style>
